# Portable terminal environment via xxh

Carries a full shell environment (fish + starship prompt) to any remote host over SSH without installing anything permanently. The remote host is left completely clean after disconnect.

## How it works

[xxh](https://github.com/xxh/xxh) uploads a self-contained shell bundle to the remote over SCP on every connect, starts the session inside it, and removes everything when you disconnect. The remote host never sees a package manager, never gets a modified `.bashrc`, and nothing persists in the home directory after you leave.

**On connect** (~51 MB uploaded via SCP every time):
- `~/.xxh/` is created on the remote
- The portable fish shell binary (`fish-portable`) is uploaded
- The starship binary and `starship.toml` config are uploaded
- The fish session config (`xxh-config.fish`) is uploaded
- The session starts with `HOME` pointing to your real home (`/home/<you>`) but all XDG dirs (`~/.config`, `~/.local`, `~/.cache`) redirected into `~/.xxh/` so nothing leaks to the real home
- The SSH alias you used to connect (e.g. `j2admin`) is forwarded as `$XXH_SSH_ALIAS` so the starship prompt can display it

**On disconnect**:
- `~/.xxh/` is deleted entirely — no files remain
- `.bashrc`, `.bash_profile`, `.profile` are never touched
- No binaries are left in `PATH`
- No processes are left running

---

## Prerequisites (local Mac)

- [xxh](https://github.com/xxh/xxh) installed via pipx
- [fish](https://fishshell.com) installed (Homebrew)
- [starship](https://starship.rs) installed (Homebrew) — macOS binary, used locally only
- Static Linux x86-64 binaries staged in `~/.xxh/bin/`:
  - `starship` — from the [starship releases page](https://github.com/starship/starship/releases) (`starship-x86_64-unknown-linux-musl.tar.gz`)
  - `fzf` — staged for future use
  - `atuin` — staged for future use
- xxh fish shell plugin installed: `xxh +I xxh-shell-fish`

---

## File layout

```
~/.config/xxh/config.xxhc           # xxh connection config (all hosts)
~/.config/starship.toml              # starship config — source of truth for both local and remote
~/.config/fish/config.fish           # local Mac fish config (starship, fzf, atuin init)
~/.config/fish/functions/xxhc.fish   # connect wrapper function

~/.xxh/ssh-wrapper.sh                # forces ControlMaster=no for rsync compat
~/.xxh/bin/starship                  # static Linux x86-64 starship binary (source)
~/.xxh/bin/fzf                       # static Linux x86-64 fzf binary (staged, unused)
~/.xxh/bin/atuin                     # static Linux x86-64 atuin binary (staged, unused)

# xxh-shell-fish local staging area — everything here is uploaded on every connect:
~/.xxh/.xxh/shells/xxh-shell-fish/build/
  entrypoint.sh                      # starts the fish session (managed by xxh, don't edit)
  fish-portable/                     # self-contained portable fish binary (~39 MB)
  xxh-config.fish                    # fish session init — sources plugins and starship
  starship.toml                      # copy of ~/.config/starship.toml
  bin/starship                       # copy of ~/.xxh/bin/starship
```

> **Two-copy rule:** `starship.toml` and `bin/starship` each live in two places. The source of truth is `~/.config/starship.toml` and `~/.xxh/bin/starship`. After changing either one, copy it into the build dir (see [Updating](#updating)).

