## Performance

Benchmarked on a connect to `j2admin` (ETH network) with `time xxhc j2admin +hc "echo ok"`:

```
Executed in   15.36 secs    fish           external
   usr time  419.69 millis  419.53 millis
   sys time  609.37 millis  608.79 millis
```

~15 seconds wall time per connect. Nearly all of that is the ~51 MB SCP upload — once files are in place the session itself starts in under a second. This cost is unavoidable with `+hhr`: every connect is a cold upload.

---

## Connecting

```sh
xxhc j2admin
```

xxh uploads ~51 MB via SCP, then drops you into a fish session. The prompt looks like:

```
tmilata @ id-s4d-s08 (j2admin) ~
›
```

- `tmilata` — your username (green)
- `@ id-s4d-s08` — actual hostname of the remote (yellow), only shown on SSH sessions
- `(j2admin)` — the SSH alias you connected with (blue), only shown via `xxhc`
- `~` — current directory relative to your real home

---

## Updating

### Starship config changed

```sh
cp ~/.config/starship.toml ~/.xxh/.xxh/shells/xxh-shell-fish/build/starship.toml
xxhc j2admin   # uploads automatically on next connect
```

### Starship binary updated

```sh
cp ~/.xxh/bin/starship ~/.xxh/.xxh/shells/xxh-shell-fish/build/bin/starship
xxhc j2admin
```

Because `+if:` and `+hhr:` are both in the config, every connect wipes the remote and re-uploads the full build dir. There is no stale cache to worry about.

---

## Uninstall

### Remove from remote

Just disconnect — `+hhr` deletes `~/.xxh` automatically.

If you connected without `+hhr` (e.g. a manual `xxh` call):

```sh
ssh <host> "rm -rf ~/.xxh"
```

### Remove everything locally

```sh
pipx uninstall xxh-xxh
rm -rf ~/.xxh ~/.config/xxh
rm ~/.config/fish/functions/xxhc.fish
```

Remove the `${env_var.XXH_SSH_ALIAS}` reference from the `format` line and the `[env_var.XXH_SSH_ALIAS]` section from `~/.config/starship.toml` to restore the plain local prompt.
